communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The contents of the training given on September 17th, 2024 at  the Manassas, VA Verizon Auditorium and developed by the George Washington University’s Program on Extremism and Combat Antisemitism Movement. I also request all communications detailing the planning for this training; the list of federal, state, and local law enforcement agencies and/or officers at the training; and any contracts that show the amount of money paid to the Combat Antisemitism Movement and the Program on Extremism for this training. Reference to this training is here: https://www.dcjs.virginia.gov/training-events/george-washington-university-program-extremism

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Alex Kane.

communications.subject: Nevada Public Records Act Request: Safety National
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All documents, correspondence, and communications—whether formal or informal—relating to the denial, partial disclaimer, or acceptance of coverage under the Safety National policy, from January 1, 2020, through the date of full compliance with this request by Safety National. This includes, but is not limited to, notices of claim determinations, letters of reservation of rights, acknowledgments of coverage, and any written affirmations or rejections of the policy’s terms as applied to submitted claims. I have attached an example.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Fecteau
